  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by concealing its true origin. Specific legal definitions vary between jurisdictions, but typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through complex financial transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into legitimate economic activities\n\nLegal definitions often include:\n- Intentionally disguising the origin of criminal proceeds\n- Transforming illegal assets into seemingly legitimate funds\n- Engaging in financial transactions to hide criminal income\n- Attempting to make illegally obtained money appear legal\n\nSpecific requirements and penalties vary by country and jurisdiction. Consulting legal professionals can provide the most accurate details for a specific location.",
